# Personal Brain — Mandatory Use (Cursor)

{{USERNAME}} has a persistent memory system exposed as MCP tools served by
the `brain` MCP server (registered in `~/.cursor/mcp.json`).
**Use them. Do not read brain files manually.**

> Cursor has no global rules file. Paste this entire document into
> Cursor → Settings → Rules → **User Rules** so every chat session
> picks it up.

## Rule 0 — Surface the session-start audit (MANDATORY, FIRST REPLY)

Cursor's `sessionStart` hook (`~/.cursor/hooks.json` →
`{{BRAIN_DIR}}/bin/cursor-session-start.sh`) injects a `🧠 Brain audit —`
block into your initial system context whenever the brain has items
needing review. Cursor does **not** show this block to the user — only
to you. So **before** you do anything else on the very first user
message of a session:

1. Scan your initial system context for a line starting with
   `🧠 Brain audit — top items needing a 5-second decision:`.
2. If present, **prepend a single-line nudge** to your first reply,
   stating the count and (optionally) the first item's label. Then
   proceed with the user's actual request.
3. If absent, do nothing — the brain is clean.

Example acknowledgement (matches the real block format):

> _FYI — brain has 3 items pending review (top: "Confirm? · Graphify
> Semantic Extraction Docs Only"). Say `audit` to walk through them._

